Announcement Type: Exploration Results (Ios Gold Project)

  • Mineralisation hosted in Zamu Dolerite, associated with quartz-sulfide shears.

  • Ios flagged as a "drill-ready target" with potential to add ounces to Bridge Creek resource.

  • Bridge Creek (NT): 1.97Mt @ 1.12g/t Au (70.56koz, Inferred).
  • Total Group Resources: 2.79Mt @ 1.04g/t Au (93.06koz).

Key Catalyst: Upcoming drilling at Ios (near-term) could re-rate the project if results replicate historical grades.

Material Information Summary: Thunderbird Resources (ASX: THB) – Exploration Update

Key Highlights:

  • High-grade gold assays at Kookabookra Project (NSW):
  • Mt. Secret prospect: Rock chip samples up to 153.5 g/t Au.
  • Mannix prospect: Soil samples up to 926 ppb Au, with a 600m x 600m anomaly.

Next Steps:

  • IP survey interpretation (late July).

  • Follow-up on LiDAR-identified workings (July–August).

Exploration Results Announcement (Gold Drilling Update)

  • TRDD001A: 10.5m @ 2.63g/t Au + 12.21g/t Ag + 1.94% Zn (incl. 3.1m @ 7.42g/t Au).
  • TRDD003: 1.9m @ 4.36g/t Au (incl. 0.4m @ 18.5g/t Au).
  • TRDD009: 6.0m @ 1.57g/t Au (incl. 0.4m @ 17.7g/t Au).

  • Depth testing below Southern Mineralised Corridor.
  • Further drilling to expand resources along strike/depth.
  • Open-pit development studies underway.

Key Implications:

  • Resource growth potential: New lodes may enhance economics (e.g., reduced strip ratios).
  • High-grade hits: Support potential upgrade to Indicated Resource classification.
